msg: This is an empty revision for padding.

author: dicka
msg: Correct problem for output parameters of simple types which are neither nillable nor optional (minOccurs="0").
These were being generated as pointer-to-pointer, however they should be pointer-to-value, to maintain consistency with input and return parameters. Particularly as these types cannot be NULL.
This change has required several testcases to be updated to match this, as they were written for the previous incorrect state.

author: dicka
msg: Modify generated complex types to allow for deep or shallow copying of simple types (defaulting to deep copy).
To ensure correct behaviour a new test case has been added: ShallowAndDeepCopyingInComplexTypeOfSimpleTypes
